OL,3,CAlcohol consumption falling, drinks
OL,4,Cindustry says
OL,6,FThe findings, published on Monday,
OL,7,Falso show that average per adult
OL,8,Falcohol consumption has declined by
OL,9,F31% since its 2001 peak.
OL,11,FWhile total alcohol consumption
OL,12,Fincreased by 0.9% in 2023 compared
OL,13,Fwith 2022, the average per person
OL,14,Fdecreased due to a 2.4% increase in
OL,15,Fthe adult population over the same
OL,16,Fperiod.
OL,18,FThe report, commissioned by the Drinks
OL,19,FIndustry Group of Ireland (DIGI),
OL,20,Fshows that average per adult alcohol
OL,21,Fconsumption decreased by 1.5%.
