OL,3,CAlcohol consumption falling, drinks
OL,4,Cindustry says
OL,6,FThis equates to 9.96 litres of pure
OL,7,Falcohol last year as opposed to
OL,8,Froughly 10.11 litres in 2022.
OL,10,FBeer is the most popular drink, making
OL,11,Fup 42.9% of all consumption in 2023,
OL,12,Fand remains the highest despite a
OL,13,Fsmall decrease on 2022 beer
OL,14,Fconsumption which stood at 43.5%.
OL,16,FWine is the second most popular at
OL,17,F28.3% of all consumption in 2023,
OL,18,Fcompared with 26.7% in 2022.
