OL,3,CAlcohol consumption falling, drinks
OL,4,Cindustry says
OL,6,FSpirits rank as the third most popular
OL,7,Fdrink with 22.6% of the 2023 total
OL,8,Fconsumption, a slight decrease on 2022
OL,9,Fwhich stood at 23.2%.
OL,11,FCider accounted for 6.2% of the 2023
OL,12,Ftotal consumption, compared with 6.6%
OL,13,Fin 2022.
OL,15,FA DIGI spokesperson said: "Overall,
OL,16,Fthe long-term decline in alcohol
OL,17,Fconsumption over the past two decades
OL,18,Findicates that Irish adults are
OL,19,Fenjoying beer, wine and spirits more
OL,20,Fmoderately and differently."
